bs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-960x420.jpg 960w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-297x130.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-800x350.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-120x53.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-768x336.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-1536x672.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-696x305.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-1068x467.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105436/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line-up_tech-details-960x420.jpg 960w\"></a></p><p>Inside, a new larger 44mm diameter ratchet ring gives the new hub series its name, now upgraded to 108 points of engagement (vs. old 72 POE) for faster power delivery. The hubs also now spin on larger axles with sealed cartridge bearings for increased strength &amp; durability, plus improved lateral stiffness.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs.jpg\" alt=\"New Spinergy 44 hubs upgrade 2021 road disc wheel line-up, freehubs\" width=\"1800\" height=\"600\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs.jpg 1800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-297x99.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-800x267.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-120x40.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-768x256.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-1536x512.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-696x232.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-1068x356.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-1260x420.jpg 1260w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs.jpg 1800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-297x99.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-800x267.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-120x40.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-768x256.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-1536x512.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-696x232.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-1068x356.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/05105406/Spinergy-44-hubs-upgrade-2021-road-disc-wheel-line_freehubs-1260x420.jpg 1260w\"></a></p><p>The new hubs still use US-made alloy cassette bodies produced by Hadley Racing Products, but now add options for: 12sp Shimano MicroSpline, 13sp Campagnolo N3W, in addition to Shimano HG, and SRAM XD &amp; XDR standards. New tool-free end caps also make it easier to swap between 15mm, 12mm &amp; QR front and 12mm &amp; QR rear axles.</p><p>For now, the disc brake only 44 hubs use centerlock rotor mounts, and while new mountain wheels aren’t yet available, Spinergy says they are making standard &amp; Boost-spaced versions of the new hubs. <em>Rim brake 44s will bring some of the same performance upgrades to rest of Spinergy’s road wheels.</em><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-4\"></span></p><h3>2021 Spinergy wheels with the new 44 hubs – Availability</h3><p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Spinergy-GXX-carbon-gravel-wheels_affordable-US-made-composite-PBO-spoke-wide-carbon-gravel-bike-wheels_wheelset.jpg\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Spinergy-GXX-carbon-gravel-wheels_affordable-US-made-composite-PBO-spoke-wide-carbon-gravel-bike-wheels_wheelset.jpg\"></p><p>As of now, two new 2021 road &amp; triathlon wheelsets – the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/09/24/ib17-spinergy-still-spinning-new-composite-aero-spokes-wider-mountain-bike-wheels/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">FCC 32 &amp; FCC47</a> – and four 2021 gravel wheelsets – <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/06/30/spinergy-gxx-laces-up-vibration-eating-composite-spoke-wide-carbon-gravel-wheels/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GXX</a>, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/04/15/spinergy-smooths-the-gravel-with-new-gx-wheels-fiber-spokes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GX</a>, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/01/27/new-spinergy-gx-max-wheels-are-built-for-extreme-gravel-adventures/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GX Max</a> 650b &amp; <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/01/27/new-spinergy-gx-max-wheels-are-built-for-extreme-gravel-adventures/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GX Max</a> 700c – already get the new disc brake version of the 44 hubs. So far the hubs are only available in black, but Spinergy has been known to produce anodized <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/06/30/spinergy-gxx-laces-up-vibration-eating-composite-spoke-wide-carbon-gravel-wheels/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">special editions</a> in the past, as well.</p><p><em>Mountain bike wheels with 44 hubs and rim brake road versions are coming soon.</em></p><p><a href=\"https://www.spinergy.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Spinergy.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ebf032391b4bf3d2598f53e4a4caa3a120c40fd547e01766f8459aec2e630b7c","category":"Cycling"}